summary: Fiona Bailey is a multi-faceted, efficient, and reliable Project Manager with over five years’ experience in delivering large complex donor aid funded education programmes. As Project Manager, she supports diverse technical teams to deliver client focussed objectives within budget and to time. She has worked across a number of countries including: South Sudan, Malawi, Rwanda, Mozambique and the Eastern Caribbean region and was educated and has lived in Europe/UK; so, fits in well in international and culturally diverse settings
